Three weeks after Katrina pets are still being rescued.
5,000 plus have been rescued but thousands have perished.
Emergency responders are voluntarily assisting but humane societies are requesting a policy that local, state and federal responders will diligently assist with pet rescues.
Representatives Lantos and Oberstar are co-sponsoring the Pets Evacuation and Transportation Standards Act to force local and state governments to create emergency evacuation plans for pets or forfeit FEMA disaster grant eligibility.
Rescued animals are being fostered in prisons and other states as local shelters are overwhelmed.
Unprecedented millions of dollars are being donated for pet rescue effort.
